<br>
I had to /beg a group that was already in the castle to let me loot PoW, even with them inside I still had trouble making it there and getting to them, they ACTUALLY had to clear the ramp for me.  The group that was inside was, 60 druid, 60 warrior, 60 wizzard, 59 paladin, 58 cleric.  Yeah they let me join their group until PoW dropped for the 4th time (first 3, as I said I couldn't of made it there w/o training them or dieing).  They had nearly a full group just to get some drops for cultural smithing, they definately weren't there for xp (heck I was 10 lvl's below them and I didn't get any xp), they weren't there for money or items (just the thing they needed for cultural smithing), they left every other mob alone.  Mind you this was nearly a full group of 60(ish) toons holding 1 room on the castle, of which all mobs were green to me 10 levels below them, and this was BEFORE the NPC caster change!?!?!?!?!!?<br>
<br>
Granted they weren't having much trouble, but they were only killing what 6 level 30(ish) casters.  Only 1 of which could drop what they needed, the others were just agro'ing them and raping them when 2 of them tried it.  Yes folks the lvl 60 warrior and 58 cleric couldn't get to the room, so they had to ask the others to come!!!!<br>
<br>
Then I hear this NPC caster change, and I will NEVER go into MM again....EVER!!!  I mean, if a 60 warrior and 58 cleric couldn't duo it, what chance would I have with jobaner BEFORE the change?  If it took 5 lvl 60(ish) toons to get into it and hold it, then what chance does Jobaner and me have, BEFORE the change?  <br>
<br>
5 lvl 60(ish) toons before NPC caster change to walk through and get to 1 room of a mid 30's zone.  Whats that going to equal TODAY?  3 full groups of 60's?<br>
<br>
Another side note, an old guild took a group to MM castle, 30 of us (2 40's groups, 2 50's groups and 1 30's group), just to get some guy a werewolf talon, some f'ing gargoyle came up and paved the road with our corpses.  THIS WAS BEFORE THE F'ING CHANGE!!!!!  Sorry, didn't catch the name of the Gargoyle, I just saw it cream the tanks and clerics in 4 seconds flat, then it proceeded to smack me around (think it was 1 cast actually). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uninjincc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ninjin CC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(6/10/02 5:25:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=240.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: um?!?</span><hr size=1> Mistmoore is another great place for trains.<br>
